        "description": {
          "value": "<p>The smaragdine golem releases an absorbed spell’s energy in a green burst centered on a point the golem can see within 60 feet of it. Each creature, other than the smaragdine golem, within 5 feet of that point per level of the absorbed spell must make a DC 18 Dexterity saving throw. On a failure, a creature takes 10 (3d6) force damage per level of the absorbed spell and is incapacitated until the end of its next turn. On a success, a creature takes half the damage and isn’t incapacitated. The golem can use this action only if it is Charged (see the Magic Vessel trait).",
